cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper is primarily focused on object recognition in computer vision systems, specifically Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the mechanisms behind object recognition in DCNNs, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The comparison between DCNNs and human recognition abilities also touches on topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
